{"sectionId":462,"sectionIdLiteral":"462","humanId":"lesson-59","volumeId":"workbook","locale":"en","titleInfo":{"ownlineNumber":"Lesson 59"},"annotation":"W-59","bodyHtml":"<div class=\"acim-text review-lesson review-1 lesson-59\"> <div data-paragraph-id=\"462#0\"><p class=\"p-review-intro\"><span data-sentence-id=\"462#0:1\">The following ideas are for review today:</span></p></div> <div data-paragraph-id=\"462#1\"><p class=\"p-lesson-ref\"><span class=\"pnr\">1.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"462#1:1\"><span class=\"snr noprint\">1</span>(<span class=\"lref\">41</span>) <b>God goes with me wherever I go.</b></span></p> <p class=\"p-normal\"><span data-sentence-id=\"462#1:2\"><span class=\"snr\">2</span>How can I be alone when God always goes with me?</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"462#1:3\"><span class=\"snr\">3</span>How can I be doubtful and unsure of myself when perfect certainty abides in Him?</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"462#1:4\"><span class=\"snr\">4</span>How can I be disturbed by anything when He rests in me in absolute peace?</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"462#1:5\"><span class=\"snr\">5</span>How can I suffer when love and joy surround me through Him?</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"462#1:6\"><span class=\"snr\">6</span>Let me not cherish illusions about myself.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"462#1:7\"><span class=\"snr\">7</span>I am perfect because God goes with me wherever I go.</span></p></div> <div data-paragraph-id=\"462#2\"><p class=\"p-lesson-ref\"><span class=\"pnr\">2.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"462#2:1\"><span class=\"snr noprint\">1</span>(<span class=\"lref\">42</span>) <b>God is my strength.</b></span> <span data-sentence-id=\"462#2:2\"><span class=\"snr\">2</span><b>Vision is His gift.</b></span></p> <p class=\"p-normal\"><span data-sentence-id=\"462#2:3\"><span class=\"snr\">3</span>Let me not look to my own eyes to see today.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"462#2:4\"><span class=\"snr\">4</span>Let me be willing to exchange my pitiful illusion of seeing for the vision that is given by God.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"462#2:5\"><span class=\"snr\">5</span>Christ‚Äôs vision is His gift, and He has given it to me.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"462#2:6\"><span class=\"snr\">6</span>Let me call upon this gift today, so that this day may help me to understand eternity.</span></p></div> <div data-paragraph-id=\"462#3\"><p class=\"p-lesson-ref\"><span class=\"pnr\">3.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"462#3:1\"><span class=\"snr noprint\">1</span>(<span class=\"lref\">43</span>) <b>God is my Source.</b></span> <span data-sentence-id=\"462#3:2\"><span class=\"snr\">2</span><b>I cannot see apart from Him.</b></span></p> <p class=\"p-normal\"><span data-sentence-id=\"462#3:3\"><span class=\"snr\">3</span>I can see what God wants me to see.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"462#3:4\"><span class=\"snr\">4</span>I cannot see anything else.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"462#3:5\"><span class=\"snr\">5</span>Beyond His Will lie only illusions.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"462#3:6\"><span class=\"snr\">6</span>It is these I choose when I think I can see apart from Him.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"462#3:7\"><span class=\"snr\">7</span>It is these I choose when I try to see through the body‚Äôs eyes.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"462#3:8\"><span class=\"snr\">8</span>Yet the vision of Christ has been given me to replace them.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"462#3:9\"><span class=\"snr\">9</span>It is through this vision that I choose to see.</span></p></div> <div data-paragraph-id=\"462#4\"><p class=\"p-lesson-ref\"><span class=\"pnr\">4.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"462#4:1\"><span class=\"snr noprint\">1</span>(<span class=\"lref\">44</span>) <b>God is the light in which I see.</b></span></p> <p class=\"p-normal\"><span data-sentence-id=\"462#4:2\"><span class=\"snr\">2</span>I cannot see in darkness.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"462#4:3\"><span class=\"snr\">3</span>God is the only light.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"462#4:4\"><span class=\"snr\">4</span>Therefore, if I am to see, it must be through Him.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"462#4:5\"><span class=\"snr\">5</span>I have tried to define what seeing is, and I have been wrong.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"462#4:6\"><span class=\"snr\">6</span>Now it is given me to understand that God is the light in which I see.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"462#4:7\"><span class=\"snr\">7</span>Let me welcome vision and the happy world it will show me.</span></p></div> <div data-paragraph-id=\"462#5\"><p class=\"p-lesson-ref\"><span class=\"pnr\">5.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"462#5:1\"><span class=\"snr noprint\">1</span>(<span class=\"lref\">45</span>) <b>God is the Mind with which I think.</b></span></p> <p class=\"p-normal\"><span data-sentence-id=\"462#5:2\"><span class=\"snr\">2</span>I have no thoughts I do not share with God.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"462#5:3\"><span class=\"snr\">3</span>I have no thoughts apart from Him, because I have no mind apart from His.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"462#5:4\"><span class=\"snr\">4</span>As part of His Mind, my thoughts are His and His Thoughts are mine.</span></p></div> </div>","firstWords":"The following ideas are for review today: (41) God goes with me wherever I go. How can I be alone when God always goes with me? How can I be doubtful and unsure of myself when perfect certainty","contentType":"acim-content","seoTitle":"Lesson 59: Review (41‚Äì45) | ACIM","seoDescription":"‚ú® A Course in Miracles with üéß Audio! Read and listen to Lesson¬†59 ‚ÄúReview (41‚Äì45)‚Äù: The following ideas are for review today: (41) God goes with me wherever I go. How can I be alone‚Ä¶","desktopBreadcrumbs":[{"label":"Workbook","leadsTo":{"locale":"en","sectionId":401,"slugs":["workbook","introduction"],"forceToc":true}},{"label":"Part I","leadsTo":{"locale":"en","sectionId":403,"slugs":["lesson-1","nothing-i-see-means-anything"],"forceToc":true}},